Our miracle baby, Benjamin 💙

Getting pregnant with Ben was a miracle. 2 doctors told me that I could no longer get pregnant and advised me to remove my uterus to decrease any risks of cancer (I had an abnormal Pap smear)

I had the surgery scheduled, and on March 20th, 2019, before being put down for anesthesia, the doctor asked me if I was absolutely sure that I didn’t want to remove my uterus. I looked at her and said that I was certain I did not want to remove my uterus and had faith that the Lord was going to give me a baby. 

Little did I know, I was already pregnant with Ben and if I had gone in to do that surgery, Ben would’ve not made and would not be here today. 

I know there are so many women who want to become mothers and it may seem impossible with your current circumstances. But I want to remind you that with God, all things are possible. If he did it for me, he can do it for you 💙
______
Nosso milagre, Benjamin 💙

Engravidar do Ben foi um milagre. 2 médicos me disseram que eu não poderia mais engravidar e me aconselharam a remover meu útero para diminuir os riscos de câncer (eu tive um exame de Papanicolaou anormal)
